-   iskustvo s Git-om;
-   entuzijazam za stjecanjem novih znanja

We are asking too much, I know... ;-)

Cyber Security Engineer

DefenseCode is providing software solutions for vulnerability analysis of web applications and their source code (DAST - Dynamic Application Security Testing and SAST - Static Application Security Testing) as well as security services which include penetration testing, source code vulnerability analysis and zero-day vulnerability research.

We are looking for a Cyber Security Engineer to take part in the development of our security software solutions and the delivery of services.

You will be skilled in multiple areas of computer security. You must have a strong sense of deadlines and be able to deliver results under pressure and in the face of uncertainty.

You will be able to handle difficult situations with composure and calm, but you must also be able to asses your own work critically.

Responsibilities:

* Penetration testing & vulnerability research
* Production of high quality penetration testing reports
* Security software development
* Production of high quality, stable and secure, well documented code
* Project and research work as needed

Basic Qualifications:

Experience of vulnerability/penetration testing and auditing techniques;
Good knowledge and understanding of security engineering, system and network security, authentication, security protocols and application security;
Experience of security software development.

Preferred Qualifications:

Experience of source code vulnerability/security testing and analysis;
Experience of C++, C# and Java, while knowledge of Perl would be especially advantageous;
Experience of code reverse engineering;
Sharp analytical abilities and good design skills;
Excellent written and verbal communication skills;
Fluency in English;
Capability of working unattended and remotely;
Ability to find solutions in the face of difficulty, ambiguity and imperfect knowledge (avoiding stall situations in the development and analysis);
Strong sense of responsibility.

Please submit your resume to jobs@defensecode.com.
